-- Gazprom Extends Declines as Putin Calls Gas Tax Insufficient
-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n   a n d   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 2012-04-17T10:43:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/gazprom-extends-declines-as-putin-calls-gas-tax-insufficient.html
OAO Gazprom extended declines after
Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  said the tax burden on  Russia ’s
natural gas producers is too low, making it “economically
unjustified.”  The shares of the country’s gas export monopoly slid as
much as 1.7 percent to 171.50 rubles after the comments by Putin
at a government meeting in Moscow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
